node.title: Brian Laundrie, sole suspect in Gabby Petito's homicide, died by suicide, lawyer confirms
node.alt: Police bodycam footage shows Mr Laundrie standing next to an officer as police pulled the couple over.
node.description: Brian Laundrie, the sole suspect in the strangulation of his girlfriend Gabby Petito during their US road trip, took his own life, according to a lawyer for his family .
node.content:
["Brian Laundrie\u00a0\u2014 the sole suspect in the death of US woman Gabby Petito \u2014 died from a\u00a0self-inflicted gunshot wound, according to a lawyer for the Laundrie family.", "He had been the subject of a manhunt for more than a month as investigators searched for clues about\u00a0the slaying of his\u00a0girlfriend, Ms Petito, during their cross-country road trip together.", "Lawyer Steve Bertolino said in a statement on Tuesday that Laundrie's parents had\u00a0been informed the cause of death was a self-inflicted gunshot wound.", "\"Chris and Roberta are still mourning the loss of their son and are hopeful that these findings bring closure to both families,\" Mr Bertolino said.", "Found in a Florida nature preserve, Mr\u00a0Laundrie's skeletal remains were positively identified last month using dental records.", "The discovery of the remains concluded a massive search involving federal, state and local law enforcement.", "It began shortly after Mr Laundrie disappeared on September\u00a014, two weeks after the 23-year-old returned alone to his parents' home in North Port, Florida.", "The investigation into Ms Petito's slaying, however, has not yet concluded.", "But only Laundrie was ever identified by police\u00a0as a person of interest in the case.", "Ms Petito's family reported the 22-year-old woman missing on September\u00a011, launching a search that attracted worldwide media attention.", "The search focused largely on the Carlton Reserve wilderness park near the Laundrie home,\u00a0a densely wooded, swampy area that is\u00a0home to alligators, coyotes, bobcats and snakes.", "Ms Petito's remains were discovered September\u00a019 on the edge of Grand Teton National Park in Wyoming, one of the places the young couple visited on the trip they documented through social media videos.", "", "
Gabby Petito was reported missing on September 11. Her remains were found eight days later.(Instagram: @gabspetito)
", "Authorities said the body had been there for about a month.", "An autopsy in Wyoming concluded Ms Petito died by strangulation and her death was a homicide.", "Mr Laundrie was listed as a \"person of interest\" in her killing but he was charged only with fraudulent use of a debit card that was not his.", "The couple had been dating since meeting in high school.", "", "
The couple frequently posted\u00a0photos on social media during their road trip.\u00a0(Supplied: Instagram @bizarre_design_)
", "AP/ABC"]
